<hl>
<seg id=1> French against change to UN Charter </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, Paris, February 14th, by Wangda Nu-The Minister of French Foreign Affairs, DeMa, pointed out that, France will not agree with changing the 5 members of the UN security council, or with restructuring the UN's basic Charter. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The French Minister of Foreign Affairs said this at the French National Foreign Affairs committee meeting yesterday. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> DeMa felt that the UN was born after the 2nd World War, France and the other Security Council members were all the winners of that war. </seg>
<seg id=5> Germany, and Italy, were the defeated countries.  Although they have now become democracies, remembering their past histories, is this enough? </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> They were reports saying that today's economically powerful countries like Germany and Japan, constantly ask for a restructuring of the UN Security Council. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The German Minister of Foreign Affairs Gunser, gave a speech on February 11th that he hoped the united Germany could play a more important role in the UN and have more say in the UN's policy decisions. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> The French Minister of Foreign Affairs responded to this and emphasized that the words of the German Minister did not reflect reality.  The members of the Security Council were decided by the UN Charter.  Changing the UN Charter should have to be approved by all the member nations of the UN, France will not agree to change the UN Charter. </seg>
</p>
